label.value: dose of irradiation that is fatal to 50% of the total study population

value.value: The amount of x-radiation that is sufficient to kill 50 percent of a population within a certain time frame.

label.value: dose of whole thorax lung irradiation that causes 50% of the total study population to have lung dysfunction

value.value: The amount of x-radiation that is sufficient to cause 50 percent of a population to have lung dysfunction (measurable as increased breathing rate or other parameter) within a certain time frame.

label.value: retinal inner nuclear layer thickness

value.value: The measurement of the thickness of the retinal layer between the inner plexiform layer and the outer plexiform layer that contains closely packed cell bodies of bipolar cells, horizontal cells, and amacrine cells.

label.value: photoreceptor inner segment thickness

value.value: This is a measurement of the inner segment of a photoreceptor. The inner segment connects the outer segment and synapse and is filled with organelles such as the ER, Golgi, and mitochondria, where much of metabolism and regulation of membrane potential takes place.

label.value: renal cortex thickness

value.value: A linear measurement of the outer part of the kidney made from the outer edge of the renal medulla to the capsule of the kidney. The cortex is composed mainly of glomeruli and convoluted tubules.

label.value: Bowman's capsule diameter

value.value: A linear measurement made from one edge to the other edge across the widest portion of a single Bowman's capsule. Bowman's capsule is the expanded portion of the nephron encircling the glomerulus.

label.value: calculated nephron measurement

value.value: Any measurement that has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the nephrons of one or both kidneys, the paired organ which functions to maintain proper water and electrolyte balance, regulate acid-base concentration, and filter the blood of metabolic wastes.

label.value: Bowman's capsule volume

value.value: A calculated estimate of the size of the three dimensional space occupied by a single Bowman's capsule in the kidney. Bowman's capsule is the expanded portion of the nephron encircling the glomerulus.

label.value: kidney glomerular density

value.value: The number of glomeruli per unit area of kidney. Based on stereological principles, the number of glomeruli per unit area of kidney equals the number of glomeruli per unit volume of kidney. Glomeruli are the tufts of capillaries each situated within a Bowman's capsule at the end of a renal tubule in the vertebrate kidney that filter waste products from the blood and thus initiate urine formation.

label.value: norepinephrine response/sensitivity measurement

value.value: Measurement of an organism's, organ's, tissue's or cell's capacity to respond, such as by a change in activity, state or condition, to norepinephrine, a catecholamine which can act as a neurotransmitter, a stress hormone and a vasoconstrictor.

label.value: norepinephrine-induced blood vessel contractile force expressed as percent of force at baseline

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the difference between the contractile force of a blood vessel in response to a specified dosage of norepinephrine and the baseline contractile force exerted by that vessel in the absence of any external stimuli, is divided by the baseline contractile force measurement and the result expressed as a percentage. Norepinephrine is a catecholamine which can act as a neurotransmitter, a stress hormone and a vasoconstrictor.

label.value: logarithm of the concentration of norepinephrine at which the force of blood vessel contraction is half the maximum value

value.value: A calculated value for logarithm of the concentration of norepinephrine at which the energy produced by the active reduction in the diameter of a blood vessel in response to the application of norepinephrine is halfway between the baseline value and the highest achievable value of such norepinephrine-induced contractile energy. The logarithm of the concentration is the exponent indicating the power to which 10 must be raised to obtain that concentration value.

label.value: ventricular late potential

value.value: The VLP is a high-frequency and very-low-intensity signal that is localized at the end of QRS duration, and on the beginning part of a ST segment.

label.value: calculated measurement of mechanical stimulus needed to elicit evasive reaction

value.value: A measurement of the pressure of liquid, gas, or solid stimulus which causes the subject to take evasive action to avoid further stimulation when that measurement has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation.

label.value: measurement of the 50% threshold of mechanical stimulus needed to elicit evasive reaction

value.value: A nociception assay is used to determine the mechanical force required to elicit a paw withdrawal response in 50% of subjects. The calculation is based on the statistical formula used to determine LD50s.

label.value: calculated platelet aggregation measurement

value.value: Measurement of the ability of platelets to aggregate in response to a known platelet aggregating factor such as collagen, ADP or thrombin which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation.

label.value: percentage of full platelet aggregation generated by thrombin

value.value: This value is calculated from an aggregometry assay curve by measuring the distance between the baseline and maximal aggregation caused by thrombin and dividing by the distance between the baseline [0% aggregation - platelet rich plasma] and 100% aggregation [platelet poor plasma].

label.value: renal plasma flow (inulin)

value.value: A measurement of the amount of plasma that perfuses the renal tubules per unit time, derived by measurement of the clearance rate of the indigestible polysaccharide inulin.

label.value: renal plasma flow (PAH)

value.value: A measurement of the amount of plasma that perfuses the renal tubules per unit time, derived by measurement of the clearance rate of the non-metabolizable solute para-aminohippurate (PAH).

label.value: ratio of renal plasma flow to kidney weight (inulin)

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the renal plasma flow rate (RPF) is divided by weight (i.e. the heaviness or the degree to which an object is drawn toward the earth by gravity) of one kidney and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage. The RPF is the amount of plasma that perfuses the renal tubules per unit time, derived by measurement of the clearance rate of the indigestible polysaccharide inulin.

label.value: ratio of renal plasma flow to kidney weight (PAH)

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the renal plasma flow rate (RPF) is divided by weight (i.e. the heaviness or the degree to which an object is drawn toward the earth by gravity) of one kidney and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage. The RPF is the amount of plasma that perfuses the renal tubules per unit time, derived by measurement of the clearance rate of the non-metabolizable solute para-aminohippurate (PAH).

label.value: percentage of study population developing ventral prostate tumorous lesions with a solid structure during a period of time

value.value: The number of individuals in a study population which develop new instances of ventral prostate tumorous lesions with a solid structure during a certain period of time compared to the total number of individuals in the study population, expressed as a percentage. Tumorous lesions include tumors, preneoplastic lesions, and hyperplastic lesions composed of histollogicaly normal cells.

label.value: percentage of study population developing ventral prostate tumorous lesions with round, irregular size nuclei during a period of time

value.value: The number of individuals in a study population which develop new instances of ventral prostate tumorous lesions with round, irregular size nuclei during a certain period of time compared to the total number of individuals in the study population, expressed as a percentage. Tumorous lesions include tumors, preneoplastic lesions, and hyperplastic lesions composed of histollogicaly normal cells.

label.value: area of individual ventral prostate tumorous lesion with a solid structure

value.value: A measurement of the extent of a two-dimensional surface of or plane through an individual tumorous lesion with a solid structure in the ventral prostate. A tumorous lesion is one which is or has the potential to become a tumor, that is, a neoplasm or new growth of tissue in which cell multiplication is more or less uncontrolled and progressive. Tumorous lesions include tumors and preneoplastic lesions, as well as hyperplastic lesions composed of histologically normal cells.

label.value: area of individual ventral prostate tumorous lesion with round, irregular size nuclei

value.value: A measurement of the extent of a two-dimensional surface of or plane through an individual tumorous lesion with round, irregular size nuclei in the ventral prostate. A tumorous lesion is one which is or has the potential to become a tumor, that is, a neoplasm or new growth of tissue in which cell multiplication is more or less uncontrolled and progressive. Tumorous lesions include tumors and preneoplastic lesions, as well as hyperplastic lesions composed of histologically normal cells.

label.value: area of ventral prostate occupied by tumorous lesions with solid structure to total ventral prostate area ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the area of the ventral prostate gland occupied by tumorous lesions with solid structure is divided by the total area of the ventral prostate gland, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage. A tumorous lesion is one which is or has the potential to become a tumor, that is, a neoplasm or new growth of tissue in which cell multiplication is more or less uncontrolled and progressive. Tumorous lesions include tumors and preneoplastic lesions, as well as hyperplastic lesions composed of histologically normal cells.

label.value: area of ventral prostate occupied by tumorous lesions with round, irregular size nuclei to total ventral prostate area ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the area of the ventral prostate gland occupied by tumorous lesions with round, irregular size nuclei is divided by the total area of the ventral prostate gland, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage. A tumorous lesion is one which is or has the potential to become a tumor, that is, a neoplasm or new growth of tissue in which cell multiplication is more or less uncontrolled and progressive. Tumorous lesions include tumors and preneoplastic lesions, as well as hyperplastic lesions composed of histologically normal cells.

label.value: number of ventral prostate tumorous lesions with solid structure

value.value: The number of tumorous lesions with solid structure in the ventral lobe of the prostate gland. A tumorous lesion is one which is or has the potential to become a tumor, that is, a neoplasm or new growth of tissue in which cell multiplication is more or less uncontrolled and progressive. Tumorous lesions include tumors, preneoplastic lesions, and hyperplastic lesions composed of histologically normal cells.

label.value: number of ventral prostate tumorous lesions with round, irregular size nuclei

value.value: The number of tumorous lesions with round, irregular size nuclei in the ventral lobe of the prostate gland. A tumorous lesion is one which is or has the potential to become a tumor, that is, a neoplasm or new growth of tissue in which cell multiplication is more or less uncontrolled and progressive. Tumorous lesions include tumors, preneoplastic lesions, and hyperplastic lesions composed of histologically normal cells.

label.value: plasma plasminogen activator inhibitor 1 level

value.value: Measurement of the amount of plasminogen activator inhibitor 1 (PAI-1) in a specified sample of plasma, the fibrinogen-containing fluid portion of the blood in which the particulate components are suspended. PAI-1 is a serine protease inhibitor protein that functions as the principal inhibitor of tissue plasminogen activator (tPA) and urokinase (uPA), the activators of plasminogen and hence fibrinolysis (the physiological breakdown of blood clots).

label.value: plasma Complement C3a des Arg  level

value.value: This is a measurement of the amount of C3a des Arg in a specified sample of plasma, the fibrinogen-containing fluid portion of the blood in which the particulate components are suspended. C3a des Arg is formed from C3a via carboxypeptidase cleavage of the C-terminal arginine group.

label.value: efferent arteriolar plasma flow rate

value.value: Volume of blood plasma delivered by a single glomerulus per unit time.

label.value: blood vitamin level

value.value: The amount of a vitamin in a specified volume of blood. A vitamin is any of various organic substances that are essential in minute quantities to the nutrition of most animals and some plants, act especially as coenzymes and precursors of coenzymes in the regulation of metabolic processes, but do not provide energy or serve as building units, and are present in natural foodstuffs or sometimes produced within the body.

label.value: blood metabolite measurement

value.value: A quantification of a parameter of a substance in the blood essential to the metabolism of a particular organism or to a particular metabolic process. In biochemistry, a metabolite is an intermediate or end product of metabolism. The term metabolite is usually used for small molecules.

label.value: subcutaneous tumor diameter measurement

value.value: The distance between two specified opposite points on the periphery of a tumor found immediately below the dermis. A tumor is an abnormal growth of tissue resulting from uncontrolled, progressive multiplication of cells and serving no physiological function.

label.value: subcutaneous tumor size measurement

value.value: Any measurement of the size of an individual tumor of the hypodermis, or of the amount of the hypodermis occupied by tumor. A tumor is an abnormal growth of tissue resulting from uncontrolled, progressive multiplication of cells and serving no physiological function.

label.value: photopic B wave amplitude of ERG waveform

value.value: Electroretinographic photopic measurement targets cone-pathway function made from the light-adapted eye. The amplitude of the b-wave is measured from the trough of the a-wave to the following peak of the b-wave. The b-wave is generated by a combination of ON- and OFF-type bipolar cells in photopic measurement.

label.value: ERG oscillatory potential

value.value: Oscillatory potentials (OPs) (four to six wavelets) can be seen on the ascending limb of most b-waves in both scotopic and photopic bright flash ERG recording. Oscillatory potentials are thought to reflect activity initiated by amacrine cells in the inner retina.

label.value: scotopic B wave amplitude of ERG waveform

value.value: Electroretinographic scotopic measurement targets rod-pathway function made from the dark-adapted eye. The amplitude of the b-wave is measured from the trough of the a-wave to the following peak of the b-wave.

label.value: scotopic A wave amplitude of ERG waveform

value.value: Electroretinographic scotopic measurement targets rod-pathway function made from the dark-adapted eye. The a-wave is the first large negative component of the electrical wave generated by the retina in response to light. The amplitude of the a-wave is measured from the baseline to the negative trough of the a-wave. If the stimulus light is weak, no scotopic A wave can be measured.

label.value: photopic A wave amplitude of ERG waveform

value.value: Electroretinographic photopic measurement targets cone-pathway function made from the light-adapted eye. The amplitude of the a-wave is typically measured from the pre-stimulus baseline (0 µV) to the trough of the a-wave. Under photopic (light-adapted) conditions, the a-wave is generated by cone photoreceptors, with additional contributions from OFF-type bipolar cells.

label.value: mean length density of glomerular capillaries

value.value: This is a calculated value based on the number of capillary profiles counted in microscopic images of glomerular tufts. The total calculated length of capillaries is expressed per glomerulus.

label.value: glomerular filtering surface area to glomerular volume ratio

value.value: This is a calculated value estimated from the glomerular filtering surface area of the peripheral capillary wall per unit glomerular volume. It is based on the proportion of the peripheral capillary basement membrane in contact with epithelial podocytes, as determined by microscopic measurements.

label.value: total filtering surface area per glomerulus

value.value: This is a calculated value estimated from the average total glomerular filtering surface area of the peripheral capillary wall per glomerulus. It is based on the proportion of the peripheral capillary basement membrane in contact with epithelial podocytes, as determined by microscopic measurements.

label.value: calculated kidney glomerular podocyte measurement

value.value: Any measurement that has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the glomerular podocytes of one or both kidneys, the paired organ which functions to maintain proper water and electrolyte balance, regulate acid-base concentration, and filter the blood of metabolic wastes.

label.value: total pericapillary slit length

value.value: This is a calculated value estimated from the glomerular filtering surface area of the peripheral capillary wall and the epithelial filtration slit frequency. The measurements for the calculations are from computerized analysis of electron micrographs.

label.value: podocyte slit width

value.value: This is an average value for the gap distance between interdigitating foot processes of podocytes in kidney glomeruli. The value is derived from the measurements of podocytes during computerized analysis of electron micrographs.

label.value: podocyte foot process width

value.value: This is a calculated value estimated from the measurement of foot processes and an equation adjusting for ambiguity of electron microscopic images of podocyte foot process boundaries.

label.value: podocyte foot process height

value.value: This is an average value of the distance between the basal side of the podocyte contacting the basement membrane and the apical side of the podocyte projecting into the urinary space. The value is derived from the measurements of podocytes during computerized analysis of electron micrographs.

label.value: mesangium volume per glomerulus

value.value: This is a calculated value made by dividing the total mesangial volume measurement by the total number of glomeruli measured, both values having been determined from measurements of microscopic images. Alternately, the fractional mesangial volume (FMV) may be multiplied by the mean glomerular volume (GV) to get the total mesangial volume (TMV).
